This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the automatic evaluation of semantic rationality of sentences. It also utilizes a language model and semantic representation to achieve this task. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the development of a neural network model for semantic rationality evaluation. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category as the proposed model is a neural network-based approach that learns from data. 

cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possible sub-category as the paper deals with the task of evaluating the semantic rationality of sentences, which is relevant to information retrieval tasks such as question answering and text summarization. 

Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category as the proposed model is a neural network-based approach.
